      <h1 class='title'>Hand Arm Vibration Syndrome</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 20 July 2004 vol 424 cc27-8WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_27ws' title='Col. 27WS &mdash; HC Deb 20 July 2004 vol 424 c27WS' name='column_27ws' href='#column_27ws' rel='bookmark'>27WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040720_CWS_27'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-jane-kennedy' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040720_CWS_27' title='Link to this speech by Ms Jane Kennedy' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-jane-kennedy" title="Ms Jane Kennedy">The Minister for Work (Jane Kennedy)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Industrial Injuries Advisory Council (IIAC) has completed its review of hand arm vibration syndrome (HAVS) and its report has been laid before Parliament (Cm 6098). The<a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_28ws' title='Col. 28WS &mdash; HC Deb 20 July 2004 vol 424 c28WS' name='column_28ws' href='#column_28ws' rel='bookmark'>28WS</a>
          Government thank the council for the care and diligence taken in producing the report, and has decided to implement the report's recommendation to widen the terms of prescription of prescribed disease A 11.</p><p>The revised prescription will take account of sensorineural symptoms, which are not included in the current prescription for prescribed disease A 11.</p><p>The Department for Work and Pensions is currently working on detailed plans for putting this report into practice, which will include communicating with those representing people who may be affected.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
